  <entry xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xml:lang="en">
    <id>http://www.coriummagazine.com/?page_id=602</id>
    <title>Demoiselle</title>
    <updated>2010-06-01</updated>
    <link href="http://www.coriummagazine.com/?page_id=602"/>
    <category term="@choice"/>
    <source>
      <id>http://www.coriummagazine.com/?page_id=602</id>
      <title>Corium Magazine</title>
    </source>
    <author>
      <name>Uche Ogbuji</name>
      <uri>http://uche.ogbuji.net</uri>
      <email>uche@ogbuji.net</email>
    </author>
    <summary type="xhtml">
      <div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
        <pre>Every bush has its berry
With soft fingers and a long tongue,
Slow, wide open like a Sunday afternoon.
But she doesn't fool me,
Alcohol all on her breath
Like a ghost in the window
Of an abandoned house.
Her hips don't tell my hands like yours.
You're a soul flame.
</pre>
      </div>
    </summary>
